Using the HTML below, write a simple ToDo List application. Let the user enter text in the text field, and when the button is clicked, you should add a new list item with the new description. Make sure to also blank out the text area for the user, and use your styling skills to make it appealing to use!

 <!doctype html>
 <html lang="en"> 
 <head>
   <meta charset="UTF-8">
   <title>Todo Application</title>
   <meta name="description" content="">
   <meta name="author" content="">
   <script type="text/javascript" src="javascript/app.js"></script>
 </head>
 <body>
     <h1>Todos</h1>
     <h2>What needs to get done today?</h2>
     <input type="text" name="nameOfItem">
     <br/>
     <input type="button" value="Add Todo">
     <br/>
     <ol id="list">
         <li>This is my first item to do!!</li>
     </ol>
 </body>
 </html>
